<LocationServicePage city="Grand Rapids" slug="electrician-grand-rapids-mi" county="Kent County, MI">
  <section class="container section-pad">
    <h2>About Electrical Service in Grand Rapids, MI</h2>
    <p>
      Grand Rapids covers the full spectrum: historic homes in Heritage Hill, Eastown, and East Grand Rapids; newer
      subdivisions on the outskirts; and a strong commercial / light-industrial base downtown and along the highways.
      Each segment has its own electrical demands.
    </p>
    <p>
      Service work in older neighborhoods often centers on panel modernization, circuit organization, and code
      corrections — older homes were not wired for today's loads. Commercial and shop work runs from LED retrofits to
      dedicated motor circuits and three-phase distribution.
    </p>

    <h3>Common Grand Rapids Projects</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Panel upgrades and service replacements in older homes</li>
      <li>Aluminum branch circuit corrections and ungrounded-outlet remediation</li>
      <li>EV charger installs (residential and small commercial)</li>
      <li>Commercial lighting retrofits and motor controls</li>
      <li>New construction wiring for residential additions and shop buildouts</li>
    </ul>

